--> local systems
   --> Docker Desktop
   --> Minikube
   --> Kubeadm

--> hosted versions available for setting up Kubernetes in a cloud environment
	
	--> Google Cloud Platform (GKE)
	--> Amazon Web Service (EKS)
	--> Microsoft Azure (AKS)

--> online platform (for practising)
	--> KodeKloud Playground

Docker Desktop
https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/
Once Installed, enable Kubernetes --> it creates a single node cluster

MiniKube
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/ 

install kubectl https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-windows/#install-kubectl-binary-on-windows-via-direct-download-or-curl
(kubectl utility works with multiple clusters at the same time)

install minikube 
https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=%2Fwindows%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2F.exe+download

make sure your system has virtualization enabled if you are using VM (skipping this step)
install vm https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads (skipping this step)


I will run Minikube on Docker as the driver.So follow below cmd
minikube start --driver=docker 

kubectl get pods -A ---> This command lists all pods across all namespaces in your Kubernetes cluster
kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx ---> creates a deployment with the name ngnix
kubectl get pods
kubectl expose deployment nginx --type=NodePort --port=80  ---> Expose nginx as a service on a random and this will open nginxâ€™s welcome page in your browser.
minikube service nginx (launches ngnix home page)
kubectl scale deployment nginx --replicas=3
minikube dashboard
minikube dashboard --url 
